# Static Qt builds (Windows default)

Zarya local and release builds on Windows should use **static Qt** unless the user explicitly asks for shared Qt.

## Configure and build

```powershell
.\scripts\configure-msvc2026.ps1 -Static
cmake --build build --config Release --target zarya
```

Or use the wrapper (static by default):

```powershell
.\scripts\build.ps1
```

Pass `-Shared` to `build.ps1` only when the user wants faster iteration with shared Qt DLLs.

## Static Qt location

- Prefix: `C:\Qt\Static\6.8.3\msvc2022_64`
- Override with `QT_STATIC_DIR` if installed elsewhere
- If missing, build once: `.\scripts\build-qt-static-msvc2026.ps1`

## Do not

- Do not configure with shared Qt (`.\scripts\configure-msvc2026.ps1` without `-Static`) for release or local builds unless the user explicitly requests shared Qt
- Do not change CMake defaults for static linking; use `-Static` on `configure-msvc2026.ps1` and `ZARYA_STATIC_QT=ON` via that script
